{"name":"The Summoner","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"class","data":{"name":"","description":"<h2>The Summoner</h2>\n<p>There are worlds beyond this one. Worlds frightening to behold, inhabited by terrible creatures of incredible power. And when you call, they answer. When you look around the campfire, do you see companions? Or are your true friends somewhere else, out beyond the stars, across a different kind of space entirely?</p>\n<p>It just figures that while you&rsquo;re out here, tackling extra-, inter-, and outer-planar threats that you&rsquo;d have to deal with all the mundanities of the prime material, like the jealousy of your fellow travellers, or the difficulties of transporting the heavy ruins of ancient magical temples.</p>\n<p>&ldquo;Just summon some big monster&rdquo; they always cry, as if you didn&rsquo;t tell them that the chaos demons of the abyss would sooner crush their skulls and magic items and the ruins into tiny pebbles than lift a big rock. Oh well. That&rsquo;s why they need you.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Names</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Elf: Janos, Sandevv, Nithenoel, Osonia, Cyithrel, Vesperr, Aell, Ellaryll</li>\n<li>Dwarf: Skagguki, Yokkaek, Ustibella, Rurragar, Khedgraes, Drufeline, Fotrunri,</li>\n<li>Human: Ash, Joey, Gaige, Orson, Rydia, Yuna, Mandrake, Rinne, Ptolemy</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Look</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>HAIR: Coiffed, curling, cascading, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>EYES: Captivating, empty, speckled, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>ROBES: Aberrant, Plain, Shimmering, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>PLANAR MARK: Runic brand, sealed bracelet, cryptic tattoo, or _ ___________</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Bonds</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>I have seen _____________ reflected across the planes - they have an vital role to play in the multiverse, and I will be their guide.</li>\n<li>______________&rsquo;s astounding ignorance means I have one more thing to worry about on this world.</li>\n<li>______________ and I will travel to other worlds after we conquer this one.</li>\n<li>I&rsquo;ve come to depend on _____________&rsquo;s expertise in the affairs of the material.</li>\n<li>I&rsquo;ve promised to scour the planes for something for _____________.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Gear</h2>\n<p>You carry these artifacts of the prime material:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Tools to make summoning circles; describe them: _________________</li>\n<li>Dungeon Rations ( 5 uses, ration, 1 weight), Uses left: 5</li>\n<li>3 Coins</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose one:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Staff ( reach, 2-handed, 1 weight)</li>\n<li>Dagger ( hand, 1 weight)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose two:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>3 healing potions ( 1 weight)</li>\n<li>16 coins</li>\n<li>Bag of books ( 5 uses, 1 weight), Uses left: 5</li>\n<li>Seeing stone ( 1 use, 1 weight): the GM will tell you what you briefly see of the coming future.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>About The Summoner</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Come Forth!\n<ul>\n<li>This move is a little dense. To summarize, when an eidolon is summoned, it&rsquo;s treated as a character, it can spend hold to make a special move related to its nature and its plane, and it has a drive that determines how it acts.</li>\n<li>On a 10+, the eidolon has two hold, +2 to one stat of the summoner&rsquo;s choice, +0 to every other stat, and the Summoner chooses the eidolon&rsquo;s drive.</li>\n<li>On a 7-9, the eidolon has one hold, +1 to one stat of the summoner&rsquo;s choice, -1 to one stat of the GM&rsquo;s choice, +0 to every other stat, and the GM chooses the eidolon&rsquo;s drive.</li>\n<li>On a 6-, an eidolon is still summoned, has one hold, and the GM can make a move. That move might include changing what stats the eidolon has or anything else about the eidolon, or the GM can choose to make any of their other moves.</li>\n<li>The eidolon does not disappear when it runs out of hold, but only when it runs out of HP.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Mundane Conjuration<br />\n<ul>\n<li>This allows the Summoner to summon objects from the material plane. Anything inanimate, nonmagical, and not too large is fair game, but this move won&rsquo;t take pieces of an object - the Summoner can&rsquo;t tunnel through rock, for example, by summoning pieces of earth out one at a time.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Let&rsquo;s Make a Deal<br />\n<ul>\n<li>This move doesn&rsquo;t require that the powerful entity is summoned via Come Forth!, although that&rsquo;s certainly an option, especially if the entity has ties to the Summoner&rsquo;s tethered plane.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Secondary School and Master&rsquo;s Degree<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Secondary School and Master&rsquo;s Degree both change the way the Summoner&rsquo;s effective Wizard level is determined. Secondary School first sets the Summoner&rsquo;s effective Wizard level to be equal to their Summoner level divided in half, and rounded up. Master&rsquo;s degree sets the Summoner&rsquo;s effective Wizard level to be one less than their Summoner level. Ex: at level 7, a Summoner with Secondary School has an effective Wizard level of 4, but a level 7 Summoner with Master&rsquo;s Degree has an effective Wizard level of 6.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>9-1-1<br />\n<ul>\n<li>The entity summoned this way is not necessarily treated as a character the Summoner controls (although it might or might not be a familiar eidolon). How it behaves and what moves it has access to is entirely up to the GM, but success on the Defy Danger roll does still imply that the threat does not come to bear (against the Summoner).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","races":{"0":{"label":"Elf","description":"Your people run deep with the magic of the forests. You can summon eidolons of the Feyhedge in addition to your tethered realm"},"1":{"label":"Dwarf","description":"When you carve your ritual circle into stone, your eidolons are summoned with +1 HP per level you have."},"2":{"label":"Human","description":"Your powerful magical connection was thrust upon you, and you have never been to your tethered plane. When you first meet a magical being, ask them one question about your plane, and they will answer it truthfully."},"3":{"label":"???","description":""}},"alignments":{"0":{"label":"Good","description":"Treat another as an equal."},"1":{"label":"Lawful","description":"Honor the wishes of one of your summons."},"2":{"label":"Evil","description":"Establish dominance over an inferior being."},"3":{"label":"???","description":""}},"equipment":{"0":{"label":"You carry these artifacts of the prime material:","mode":"checkbox","items":["F1Op2wZodNPLsi6z","6JcOoZ8CNqYxLgyQ"]},"1":{"label":"Choose one:","mode":"radio","items":["nMag6sXXRqc6SC4Q","xu45M9oglN3VEWHC"]},"2":{"label":"Choose two:","mode":"checkbox","items":["CMhNmAwhLVZk9lfq","iaxOPwJIrsnzGJWr","FV1Z8J3c1yeDwCRb"]}},"hp":4,"load":7},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GsqBf792Fp33d3am"}
