{"name":"Tetherer","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Tetherer</p>\n<p>When you have time, arcane materials, and a safe space in a plane, you may tether yourself to that plane, and summon eidolons from it with Come Forth!</p>\n<p>The GM will tell you who is angered or interested in this tether.</p>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4HdltxGyVd7rMkKd"}
{"name":"Tethered Plane","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Tethered Plane</p>\n<p>You are connected to another realm with binding magic.</p>\n<p>Choose a plane from the list below.</p>\n<p>You can summon beings from this realm, and they will show you at least a semblance of attention.</p>\n<p>You can speak with denizens of your tethered plane.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The Four Elemental Planes</li>\n<li>The Abyss, pit of demons</li>\n<li>Valhalla, hall of fallen warriors</li>\n<li>Celestia, mountain of godly champions</li>\n<li>Mechanus, clockwork kingdom of law</li>\n<li>Carceri, six demiplanes of eternal prison</li>\n<li>Feyhedge, the thorny ethereal wilds</li>\n<li>Pandemonium, endless maze of chaos and shapeshifters</li>\n</ul>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"slDPHRuhMWfh3z8w"}
{"name":"Come Forth!","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Come Forth! (INT)</p>\n<p>When you incant for a few minutes over a ritual circle, roll+INT and you summon an eidolon from your tethered plane.</p>\n<p>Treat this eidolon as a character you control with 1 HP per level you have, +0 to each stat, access to all the basic moves, and 1 hold that it can spend to make a move related to its plane.</p>\n<p>It uses your damage die. It doesn&rsquo;t have an alignment - instead it has a drive, related to its plane of origin.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, you choose its drive and it has +2 to a stat of your choice and an additional hold (2 hold total).</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, the GM chooses its drive, and you pick a stat it has +1 in and the GM will choose a stat it has -1 in.</p>\n<p>On a 6-, you still summon an eidolon in addition to whatever the GM says.</p>\n<p>When the eidolon runs out of HP, it disappears, whisked back to your tethered plane. You can have only one eidolon at a time - if you already have an eidolon at your command in this plane of existence, this move won&rsquo;t trigger.</p>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"INT","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dZyKsid6n98W0eSO"}
{"name":"Whence You Came!","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Whence You Came! (WIS)</p>\n<p>When you banish a weakened or vulnerable creature to its native plane, roll+WIS.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, the creature is sent back to its plane of origin.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, it&rsquo;s banished, but it takes something with it.</p>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"WIS","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"tyy2EePPzCStgXkW"}
{"name":"Mundane Conjuration","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Mundane Conjuration (INT)</p>\n<p>When you bring forth a nonliving, nonmagical object no heavier than yourself, roll+INT.</p>\n<p>On a hit, the object appears in a location of your choice within a few feet of you.</p>\n<p>On a 10+, choose two.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, choose one.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>It&rsquo;s exactly what you wanted</li>\n<li>It doesn&rsquo;t come from somewhere close</li>\n<li>Nothing else comes with it</li>\n</ul>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"INT","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":0,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"starting","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gatPfOVhLC7X8xWX"}
{"name":"Esper Crash","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Esper Crash</p>\n<p>You take +1 to banish your eidolon, and your eidolon is always vulnerable to you.</p>\n<p>When you banish your eidolon, it deals its damage to everything in the area, even on a miss.</p>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HUNgY85Ts70qhW2Z"}
{"name":"Let’s Make a Deal","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Let&rsquo;s Make a Deal</p>\n<p>When you strike a deal of servitude with a powerful being, roll+CHA.</p>\n<p>On a 10+ they agree to be summoned in a future time of aid.</p>\n<p>On a 7-9, they will require you to aid them before they aid you.</p>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"CHA","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4kNiUY9WkLzTNnEg"}
{"name":"Vivid Storyteller","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Vivid Storyteller</p>\n<p>When you bring a character to life by reading a passage aloud, you may trigger Come Forth! and roll+CHA instead of INT.</p>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2VpuQ6ANeA9eFtDb"}
{"name":"Power Word: Summon","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Power Word: Summon</p>\n<p>You can trigger the move Call Forth by just whispering a few words of incantation.</p>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"70as6bjg7eUU11IW"}
{"name":"Harder Better Faster Stronger","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Harder Better Faster Stronger</p>\n<p>When you summon an eidolon, choose [[/r 1d4]].</p>\n<ul>\n<li>It&rsquo;s large; it deals +[[/r 1d4]] damage</li>\n<li>It&rsquo;s well-equipped; it deals +1 damage and has +1 armor</li>\n<li>It has a strong connection to this world; it has +[[/r 2d4]] HP&nbsp;</li>\n<li>It&rsquo;s powerful; +2 hold</li>\n</ul>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AcxDPXZq9tJi004F"}
{"name":"Evocation Specialist","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Evocation Specialist</p>\n<p>When you unleash the primal energies of your tethered plane, roll+WIS.</p>\n<p>On a 10+ choose two.</p>\n<p>7-9, choose one.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The effect you desire comes to pass</li>\n<li>You avoid paying your plane&rsquo;s price</li>\n<li>You retain control</li>\n</ul>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"WIS","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wTHVkNWPG30QzLhS"}
{"name":"Secondary School","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Secondary School</p>\n<p>You gain the Cast a Spell, Prepare Spells, and Spellbook moves from the Wizard playbook.</p>\n<p>When preparing spells, treat your Wizard level as your level divided by two, rounded up.</p>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":2,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6OmWhnMu9Zl7ImKr"}
