{"name":"Unshackled","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Unshackled</p>\n<p>When you sever the planar magic binding an eidolon to you, they are freed to pursue their own agenda.</p>\n<p>They become a GM character, and you can never summon them again with Come Forth.</p>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aLC3SG9zFbFOFVjf"}
{"name":"Well Connected","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Well Connected</p>\n<p>Working with the GM, create a legendary planar entity with special moves and assign it these stats: +3, +2, +1, +1, 0, -1.</p>\n<p>On a 12+ with Come Forth, you summon that entity for free.</p>\n<p>On a 10-11, you may choose to offer something to the entity in order to summon it.</p>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vCIqtEK7hPdXH7H3"}
{"name":"Master’s Degree","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"move","data":{"name":"","description":"<p>Master&rsquo;s Degree</p>\n<p>Requires: Secondary School</p>\n<p>You now prepare spells as though you were a Wizard of one level below your actual level.</p>\n<p>You prepare spells of the Summoning school as though they were two levels lower.</p>","class":"The Summoner","rollType":"","rollMod":0,"requiresLevel":6,"requiresMove":"Secondary School","moveType":"advanced","moveGroup":""},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oLW2MOhwL7W919or"}
